Sure, here's the reframed code to generate the log message in JSON format:

```java
import com.google.gson.Gson;
import com.google.gson.GsonBuilder;

public void writeLogToFile(FileMetadata metadata, String destinationFolderPath) {
    String logFilePath = destinationFolderPath + "/log.txt";
    Gson gson = new GsonBuilder().create();
    try (FileWriter fileWriter = new FileWriter(logFilePath, true)) {
        String jsonMetadata = gson.toJson(metadata);
        fileWriter.write(jsonMetadata);
        fileWriter.write(System.lineSeparator());
        fileWriter.flush();
    } catch (IOException e) {
        LOGGER.error("Error writing log to file", e);
    }
}
```

For the dependencies, you need to add the Gson library to your pom.xml file:

```xml
<dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>com.google.code.gson</groupId>
        <artifactId>gson</artifactId>
        <version>2.8.8</version>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>
```

Make sure to include the necessary dependencies and update your pom.xml file accordingly.